<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/1384931-eliece"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1514600888i/1384931._UX100_CR0,13,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/1384931-eliece">Eliece</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">It&apos;s not Italian cooking, but the wonderful Bruno books by Martin Walker are set in the Dordogne area of France, and are mysteries that feature lots a<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">It's not Italian cooking, but the wonderful Bruno books by Martin Walker are set in the Dordogne area of France, and are mysteries that feature lots about cooking. Try them. This book reminded me very much of them, and they are a series, so should keep you happy for a while. I actually liked them even more.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
