<span id="freeTextContainer14420865449103260794">I received this from netgalley.com in exchange for a review. <br/><br/>In 1944, pilot Hugo Langley parachuted from his plane into the fields of German-occupied Tuscany. Badly wounded, he found refuge in a ruined monastery and in the arms of Sofia Bartoli. 1973, Hugo’s estranged daughter, Joanna, has returned home to the English countryside to arrange her father’s funeral and travels to Italy to discover his past.<br/><br/>For me, books written in duo timelines can be a hit or miss. This time, neither timeline was b</span>
  <span id="freeText14420865449103260794" style="display:none">I received this from netgalley.com in exchange for a review. <br /><br />In 1944, pilot Hugo Langley parachuted from his plane into the fields of German-occupied Tuscany. Badly wounded, he found refuge in a ruined monastery and in the arms of Sofia Bartoli. 1973, Hugo’s estranged daughter, Joanna, has returned home to the English countryside to arrange her father’s funeral and travels to Italy to discover his past.<br /><br />For me, books written in duo timelines can be a hit or miss. This time, neither timeline was better - or worse - than the other. The story read in ebbs and flows. Highs and lows.<br /><br />3☆</span>
